added.title: Tweety-Go-Round
added.description: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

added.title: Smash House
added.description: The Looney Builders learn that Taz accidentally destroyed his house, so they set out to build him a new one that's smash-proof.

added.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
added.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

added.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
added.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

added.title: Sir Topham Hatt's Hat
added.description: When Sir Topham Hatt's Hat blows away in the wind before making an important announcement, Thomas and his friends race around Sodor, trying to catch it. The Hat remains out of reach until they learn to work together.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Nia's Surprising Surprise
added.description: Nia is planning a big party to celebrate the anniversary of her arrival on Sodor, but she finds that her friends don't remember her anniversary and are too busy to even talk about it.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Garbage Truck
added.description: Blippi and TABBS shrink down and fly into a garbage truck where they meet Horace, a singing and dancing fly, who shows them what he loves to eat--garbage!

added.title: Australia Kangaroo
added.description: Blippi stumbles across a Kangaroo Crossing sign in Australia and wonders "How high can a kangaroo jump?" His new kangaroo mate Rudy is happy to demonstrate, challenging Blippi to a hopping race around the famous sandstone monolith Uluru. Can Blippi jump as high as a kangaroo?

added.title: Get Active Dance
added.description: Mei, Ella, animals and vegetables have a farm active day exercising and organising the farm

added.title: Salad Salsa
added.description: Mei, Ella, animals cook a delicious salad using local vegetables

added.title: The Wheel Deal
added.description: Everyone's excited about a grand bicycle outing through the park, everyone except Tweety whose little legs don't quite reach the pedals. Frustrated after riding on the back of Floyd's bicycle while everyone else has fun, Tweety is ready to go home.

added.title: Oh Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?
added.description: Baby Sylvester is overcome with angst because Granny's broken old chair, his favorite napping place, must be replaced by a new, unfamiliar piece of furniture. The other Baby Looney Tunes work together to help turn Sylvester's trepidation into enjoyment during their mammoth furniture-shopping adventure.

added.title: Baby Brouhaha
added.description: Overhearing Granny on the phone say she's expecting a baby, Baby Bugs goes into overdrive, revving up the Baby Looney Tunes to prepare to care for an infant.

added.title: Blast Off Bugs
added.description: Baby Bugs tries to realize his dream of traveling to the moon while the Baby Looney Tunes are on a space museum visit.

added.title: Flu the Coop
added.description: Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy decide to team up and unlike the other Baby Looney Tunes, fake having received their annual flu shots at the local clinic. The joke's on them when they awaken on the day of Granny's big party unable to have fun because they both have the flu.

added.title: Unlock the Magic: The Beginning
added.description: The discovery of an ancient, lost gateway leads the Care Bears on a rescue mission in the Silver Lining, a realm of natural wonders and comical creatures in the clouds beyond the borders of Care-A-Lot. While there, new discoveries expand the mission, challenging Cheer, Grumpy, and the mission team to grow beyond their present abilities and help the denizens of the Silver Lining.

added.title: A Patch of Perturbed Petunias
added.description: Share fears she's losing her ability as a problem-solver and peacemaker when she can't calm a squabble between a group of Whiffles and a flower bed of Perturbed Petunias. Cheer discovers it's not Share's fault; the Petunias are being secretly manipulated by Bluster's rumor-mongering.

added.title: Nobody's Perfect
added.description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

added.title: A Yoorg Awakening
added.description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

added.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
added.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

removed.title: Please and Thank You Song
removed.description: Mei goes around the farm with food for the animals. She offers them some food and the animals say "yes please"

removed.title: Win, Lose or Daffy
removed.description: A day playing miniature golf is fun for everyone but Baby Daffy, who believes he must beat everyone else at the game. At the end of the day, all but Daffy are having a good time regardless of how they scored.

removed.title: There's Nothing Like a Good Book
removed.description: A nagging question regarding the composition of the moon brings the Baby Looney Tunes to experience their very first visit to the library.

removed.title: Wrong!
removed.description: On an orchard outing, picking bushels of fresh apples for Granny's home-baked pies, the Baby Looney Tunes encounter Melissa, who is in a mood to tell everyone that her method of apple picking is the only way.

removed.title: The Great Giggle
removed.description: The Care Bears are to witness the annual blooming of the Pinata Tree, an ancient event that can only happen if the Keeper of the Tree sees something that makes him giggle. Good Luck's giggle-inducing entertainment act goes awry because he relies on his errant lucky shamrock for success. He must learn to forgo luck and practice his act instead.

removed.title: Funshine's Un-fun Day
removed.description: Funshine can't bring himself to tell Cheer he accidentally broke her beloved necklace. His attempts to repair the broken necklace end in failure, so he hides it. When Cheer wrongly thinks Dibble is responsible for the disappearance of the necklace, Funshine knows he must tell her the truth.

removed.title: Play Day
removed.description: When the Looney Builders build themselves a playground, Daffy gets so excited about his section that he takes all the supplies for himself.

removed.title: Mixed Signals
removed.description: The team receives a video message from Tenderheart that their mission has successfully ended and they can return home. Cheer suspects something about the message is wrong, but other members of the team don't agree. Cheer courageously stands her ground and keeps the team together while she solves the mystery, and reveals the message was faked by Bluster.

removed.title: A Turtle Named Mrytle
removed.description: A trip to the seashore brings the Baby Looney Tunes into contact with a just-hatched turtle that Melissa, apart from the rest because of her bossy attitude, names Myrtle. Melissa just loves little Myrtle and wants to keep her from walking into the ocean so she may take Myrtyle home for herself.

removed.title: The Treasure of Treetop Woods/Zee Makes an Amazing Maze!
removed.description: Ranger Nat's hike turns to adventure when he finds a treasure map. The only problem is that he can't read it./Zee and MacBarm are setting up their corn maze with the help of Zee's Zee Mobile… that is, until it breaks down inside the maze.

removed.title: Splash Zone
removed.description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

removed.title: Yip Yip, Book Book!/Stick to It!
removed.description: It's the Pretty Big All City Read and Izzy and Barb are ready, that is, until all the books go missing!/Pretty Big City finds itself in a sticky situation when the factory starts spewing super sticky slime everywhere!

removed.title: Sneeze
removed.description: What is making Blippi sneeze? What makes anyone sneeze? Blippi shrinks down and flies up a nose to find out! A very mischievous piece of pollen demonstrates how to make a sneeze happen, resulting in Blippi himself getting blown away by a giant sneeze!

removed.title: Skiff Sails Sodor
removed.description: When Skiff gets a crack in his hull, Thomas needs to move him overland to Harwick for repairs, but Skiff's land-sickness makes that challenging.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: A New View for Thomas
removed.description: When Thomas spends the day carrying rockstar idol Harold across Sodor, he gains a new perspective on just how amazing it is to be his engine-self.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Baa Baa Black Sheep
removed.description: It's getting chilly on the farm! Summers dwindled into autumn and everyone is in need of some winter clothing

removed.title: The Big Whifflesnooze
removed.description: Cheer, distracted by other work, doesn't give her complete attention to a problem with the Whiffles. The mistake starts a chain of comical events that results in the Whiffles going into a one-hundred-year sleep that can only be rectified by an ancient chant.

removed.title: The Dolly Vanishes
removed.description: On an overnight train trip to visit Floyd at college, Lola's doll vanishes. Baby Bugs acts as a detective as he tries to solve the missing Edna mystery via a series of simple flashbacks, seen from each Baby Looney Tunes' point of view.

removed.title: Spiderweb
removed.description: A gorgeous spider web in the park has Blippi wondering "How do spiders make their webs?" He sets off to find the answer! A very talented spider explains the artistic process and Blippi is surprised by the masterful picture that ends up in the spiders' web!

removed.title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
removed.description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.
